This paper is about improving machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new training method that involves generating training examples with model predictions as part of their inputs, which is a machine learning technique. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which is a common technique in deep learning, and could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on machine translation tasks, which could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as machine translation involves processing and generating images of text.
